overview: The user requested a thorough browser-based test of the sleep
  questionnaire application. The agent began by checking the dev server and
  navigating the application. It successfully tested the "Pre-fill & Jump to
  Report (Dev)" functionality, confirming that the report section was eventually
  reached and that PDF generation worked correctly. The agent also tested the
  admin login, verifying that error handling for incorrect passwords was in
  place. However, significant issues were found with the questionnaire's section
  navigation. Clicking "Next Section" or "Previous" often resulted in no visible
  change, or unexpected jumps to different sections, indicating potential state
  management or rendering bugs. Despite these navigation challenges, conditional
  fields within the form were observed to be working as intended. The agent
  noted the absence of console errors related to the navigation issues,
  suggesting a more subtle problem within the application's logic.
